"title": "5059: rest, eternal",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5059: rest, eternal",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Eternal rest consists of peace with God, an absence of toil and tribulation and a final deliverance from pain, sorrow and death. It is promised as the inheritance of the people of God.</p>\n<h2>Eternal rest foreshadowed in the OT</h2>\n<h3>In God's rest after creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:3-Heb4:4\">HEB 4:3–4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:2-Gen2:3\">GEN 2:2–2:3</a></p>\n<h3>In the rest promised to Joshua</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:8\">HEB 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:7\">DEU 31:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:4\">JOS 22:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:7-Ps95:11\">PSA 95:7–95:11</a></p>\n<h2>The eternal state described as rest</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:9\">HEB 4:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:11-Job3:19\">JOB 3:11–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:13\">REV 14:13</a></p>\n<h2>Aspects of eternal rest</h2>\n<h3>Being in the presence of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:43\">LUK 23:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:3\">JHN 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:23\">PHP 1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:17-1Thess4:18\">1TH 4:17–4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:4\">REV 3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:15\">REV 7:15</a></p>\n<h3>Happiness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:8\">2CO 5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:23\">MAT 25:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:29\">LUK 13:29</a></p>\n<h3>Refreshment and satisfaction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:17\">REV 7:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:11\">PSA 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:15\">PSA 17:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:1-Ezek47:12\">EZK 47:1–47:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:1-Rev22:2\">REV 22:1–22:2</a></p>\n<h3>The absence of trouble</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:6-2Thess1:7\">2TH 1:6–1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:10-Rev6:11\">REV 6:10–6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:14\">REV 7:14</a></p>\n<h3>The absence of labour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:13\">REV 14:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:17\">JOB 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:2\">ISA 57:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:22-Isa65:23\">ISA 65:22–65:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:1-Heb4:11\">HEB 4:1–4:11</a></p>\n<h3>The absence of pain, sorrow and death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:4\">REV 21:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:8\">ISA 25:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:19\">ISA 65:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:36\">LUK 20:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:23\">ROM 8:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:24\">1CO 15:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:16-Rev7:17\">REV 7:16–7:17</a></p>\n<h3>The absence of conflict and harm</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:25\">ISA 65:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:6-Isa11:9\">ISA 11:6–11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:18\">HOS 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>The absence of the curse</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:3\">REV 22:3</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Eternal rest is conditional upon faithful obedience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:11\">HEB 4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:1-Heb4:2\">HEB 4:1–4:2</a></strong></p>",
